<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Demand Gen heavy-up — 2026-04-20 readout</title>
<script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/chart.js@4.4.1/dist/chart.umd.min.js"></script>
<style>
  :root {
    --navy: #13213C;
    --navy-2: #1E3665;
    --red: #A21E22;
    --gold: #C8A646;
    --green: #2E7D32;
    --gray-50: #F7F8FA;
    --gray-100: #EEF0F4;
    --gray-200: #DCE0E8;
    --gray-400: #8B92A3;
    --gray-600: #525868;
    --gray-900: #1A1E28;
    --shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(19,33,60,0.04), 0 4px 12px rgba(19,33,60,0.06);
    --shadow-lg: 0 4px 8px rgba(19,33,60,0.06), 0 12px 32px rgba(19,33,60,0.08);
    --radius: 12px;
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  html, body {
    margin: 0; padding: 0;
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
    background: var(--gray-50);
    color: var(--gray-900);
    -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
  }
  a { color: var(--navy-2); }
  .wrap { max-width: 1280px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 28px 80px; }

  /* Header */
  header.top {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--navy) 0%, var(--navy-2) 100%);
    color: #fff;
    padding: 36px 28px 44px;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  header.top .eyebrow {
    font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  header.top h1 {
    margin: 0 0 6px 0; font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  header.top .sub {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78); font-size: 15px; max-width: 780px;
  }
  header.top .meta-row {
    margin-top: 20px; display: flex; gap: 24px; flex-wrap: wrap;
    font-size: 13px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.78);
  }
  header.top .meta-row b { color: #fff; font-weight: 600; }

  /* Layered section labels */
  .layer-label {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 700; padding: 4px 10px; border-radius: 999px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .layer-exec { background: rgba(162,30,34,0.08); color: var(--red); }
  .layer-tac  { background: rgba(30,54,101,0.08); color: var(--navy-2); }
  .layer-deep { background: rgba(138,138,138,0.14); color: var(--gray-600); }

  /* KPI grid */
  .kpi-grid {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .kpi-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); } }
  .kpi {
    background: #fff; border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 20px 22px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow); border: 1px solid var(--gray-100);
    position: relative;
  }
  .kpi .label { font-size: 12px; color: var(--gray-600); font-weight: 500; letter-spacing: 0.02em; }
  .kpi .val { font-size: 34px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--navy); line-height: 1.1; margin-top: 6px; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .kpi .delta { margin-top: 6px; font-size: 12px; color: var(--gray-600); }
  .kpi .delta.up { color: var(--green); }
  .kpi .delta.down { color: var(--red); }
  .kpi.hero { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--navy) 0%, var(--navy-2) 100%); color: #fff; }
  .kpi.hero .label { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.72); }
  .kpi.hero .val { color: #fff; }
  .kpi.hero .delta { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.82); }
  .kpi .pass-badge {
    display: inline-block; margin-top: 8px; padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 4px;
    font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .kpi .pass-badge.pass { background: rgba(46,125,50,0.14); color: var(--green); }
  .kpi .pass-badge.fail { background: rgba(162,30,34,0.14); color: var(--red); }

  /* Cards */
  .card {
    background: #fff; border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 22px 24px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow); border: 1px solid var(--gray-100);
    margin-bottom: 22px;
  }
  .card h2 {
    margin: 0 0 4px 0; font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--navy);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .card h3 {
    margin: 28px 0 6px 0; font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--navy);
  }
  .card .card-sub {
    color: var(--gray-600); font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 20px;
    max-width: 780px; line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Controls */
  .controls {
    display: flex; gap: 8px; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
  .toggle-group {
    display: inline-flex; background: var(--gray-100); border-radius: 8px; padding: 3px;
  }
  .toggle-group button {
    background: transparent; border: none; padding: 7px 14px; font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500; color: var(--gray-600); border-radius: 6px;
    cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.15s;
  }
  .toggle-group button.active { background: #fff; color: var(--navy); box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(19,33,60,0.08); font-weight: 600; }
  .toggle-group button:hover:not(.active) { color: var(--navy); }

  /* Chart containers */
  .chart-box { position: relative; width: 100%; }
  .chart-box.h300 { height: 300px; }
  .chart-box.h360 { height: 360px; }
  .chart-box.h420 { height: 420px; }
  .two-col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 22px; }
  @media (max-width: 900px) { .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  /* Week scrubber */
  .scrubber { margin-top: 8px; }
  .scrubber label { font-size: 12px; color: var(--gray-600); font-weight: 500; }
  .scrubber input[type="range"] {
    width: 100%; margin-top: 8px; accent-color: var(--navy-2);
  }
  .scrubber-readout {
    margin-top: 14px; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 12px;
    background: var(--gray-50); border-radius: 8px; padding: 14px 16px;
  }
  .scrubber-readout .sr-item .l { font-size: 11px; color: var(--gray-600); letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 600; }
  .scrubber-readout .sr-item .v { font-size: 20px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--navy); margin-top: 2px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
  .scrubber-readout .sr-item .d { font-size: 11px; color: var(--gray-600); margin-top: 1px; }

  /* Click-to-reveal math */
  details.math {
    margin-top: 12px; background: var(--gray-50); border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }
  details.math[open] { background: #fff; border-color: var(--gray-200); }
  details.math summary {
    padding: 12px 16px; cursor: pointer; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--navy-2); list-style: none;
  }
  details.math summary::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
  details.math summary::before { content: "▸ "; color: var(--gray-400); transition: transform 0.2s; display: inline-block; }
  details.math[open] summary::before { content: "▾ "; color: var(--navy-2); }
  details.math .math-body {
    padding: 4px 18px 18px; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--gray-900);
  }
  details.math .math-body code {
    background: var(--gray-100); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px;
    font-family: "SF Mono", Consolas, "Liberation Mono", monospace; font-size: 12.5px;
  }
  details.math .math-body table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 10px; font-size: 12.5px; }
  details.math .math-body th, details.math .math-body td { text-align: right; padding: 6px 10px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-200); }
  details.math .math-body th:first-child, details.math .math-body td:first-child { text-align: left; }
  details.math .math-body th { color: var(--gray-600); font-weight: 600; font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }

  /* Tables */
  table.dtable { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px; }
  table.dtable th, table.dtable td {
    padding: 9px 10px; text-align: right; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-100);
  }
  table.dtable th { font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: var(--gray-600); font-weight: 600; background: var(--gray-50); }
  table.dtable th:first-child, table.dtable td:first-child { text-align: left; }
  table.dtable td.pos { color: var(--green); font-weight: 600; }
  table.dtable td.neg { color: var(--red); font-weight: 600; }
  table.dtable tbody tr:hover { background: var(--gray-50); }

  /* TL;DR callout */
  .tldr {
    background: #fff; border-left: 4px solid var(--red);
    border-radius: 4px 12px 12px 4px; padding: 20px 24px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow); margin-bottom: 28px;
    font-size: 15.5px; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--gray-900);
  }
  .tldr b { color: var(--navy); }
  .tldr .tldr-label { display: block; font-size: 11px; color: var(--red); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.12em; margin-bottom: 8px; }

  /* Comments card */
  .comments-card {
    background: #fff; border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
    border-radius: 4px 12px 12px 4px; padding: 20px 24px;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow); margin-bottom: 28px;
  }
  .comments-card .comments-label {
    display: block; font-size: 11px; color: var(--gold); font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em; margin-bottom: 8px; text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .comments-card .comments-empty {
    color: var(--gray-400); font-style: italic; font-size: 15px;
  }

  /* Flags */
  .flag-list { margin: 12px 0 0 0; padding-left: 0; list-style: none; }
  .flag-list li {
    padding: 10px 14px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-radius: 8px;
    font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.55;
    background: var(--gray-50); border-left: 3px solid var(--gray-400);
  }
  .flag-list li.watch { border-left-color: var(--gold); background: rgba(200,166,70,0.08); }
  .flag-list li.resolved { border-left-color: var(--green); background: rgba(46,125,50,0.06); }
  .flag-list li.issue { border-left-color: var(--red); background: rgba(162,30,34,0.06); }
  .flag-list li b { color: var(--navy); }

  /* Gauge */
  .gauge-wrap {
    display: flex; gap: 22px; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .gauge-box { flex: 0 0 280px; }

  /* Footer */
  footer.foot {
    margin-top: 40px; padding-top: 20px; border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-200);
    font-size: 12px; color: var(--gray-600);
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px;
  }
  footer.foot a { color: var(--navy-2); text-decoration: none; }
  footer.foot a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  /* Decision card */
  .decision {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(46,125,50,0.06) 0%, rgba(46,125,50,0.02) 100%);
    border: 1px solid rgba(46,125,50,0.22);
    border-radius: 10px; padding: 16px 20px; margin-top: 14px;
  }
  .decision .head { font-size: 11px; color: var(--green); font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .decision .body { font-size: 15px; color: var(--gray-900); margin-top: 4px; line-height: 1.5; }

  /* Smaller hint text */
  .hint { font-size: 12px; color: var(--gray-600); margin-top: 6px; }

  /* Nav bar */
  .nav-bar {
    background: var(--navy); padding: 10px 24px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px;
  }
  .nav-bar a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); text-decoration: none; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600;
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; transition: color 0.15s;
  }
  .nav-bar a:hover { color: #fff; }
  .nav-bar .sep { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.3); font-size: 13px; }
  .nav-bar .current { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 400; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<nav class="nav-bar">
  <a href="index.html">← All studies</a>
  <span class="sep">|</span>
  <span class="current">Demand Gen heavy-up</span>
</nav>

<div class="wrap">

  <!-- HEADER -->
  <header class="top">
    <div class="eyebrow">Geo incrementality test · Demand Gen heavy-up</div>
    <h1>Google Demand Gen — the headline flipped positive</h1>
    <div class="sub">A live, interactive readout of the 2026-04-20 weekly refresh. 51 treatment DMAs, 51 control DMAs, +75% spend-up, 6 weeks of trimmed data, 44 days full window.</div>
    <div class="meta-row">
      <span><b>Test:</b> <span id="m-test">—</span></span>
      <span><b>Analysis date:</b> <span id="m-ad">—</span></span>
      <span><b>Data through:</b> <span id="m-dt">—</span></span>
      <span><b>Trimmed window:</b> <span id="m-tw">—</span></span>
      <span><b>Full window:</b> <span id="m-fw">—</span></span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ============ LAYER 1: EXECUTIVE ============ -->

  <div class="comments-card" id="eric-comments">
    <span class="comments-label">Eric's Executive TL;DR</span>
    <iframe src="demand_gen_heavyupdate-20260420-comments.txt" class="comments-frame"
      style="width:100%; border:none; overflow:hidden; display:block;"
    ></iframe>
  </div>
  <script>
  document.querySelector('#eric-comments .comments-frame').addEventListener('load', function(){
    try {
      var b = this.contentDocument.body;
      b.style.cssText = 'margin:0;padding:0;font:15px/1.7 -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,Segoe UI,Roboto,Helvetica Neue,Arial,sans-serif;color:#1A1E28;white-space:pre-wrap;word-wrap:break-word;';
      var resize = function(frame, body) {
        frame.style.height = 'auto';
        frame.style.height = Math.max(24, body.scrollHeight) + 'px';
      };
      resize(this, b);
      setTimeout(function(){ resize(this, b); }.bind(this), 100);
      setTimeout(function(){ resize(this, b); }.bind(this), 500);
    } catch(e){}
  });
  </script>

  <div class="tldr">
    <span class="tldr-label">Claude Overview</span>
    Matched-markets Orders iROAS cleared the <b>1.4x GP floor</b> at <b>1.46x</b>
    with effectively 100% confidence, and this run's incremental GP dollars concentrate in
    <b>new-to-file customers</b> — NTF new-customer GP roughly doubled week-over-week.
    Recommendation: <b>continue the heavy-up</b> and consider a modest additional step-up.
    Primary watch item: GA4 DG LC ROAS stayed above the <b>0.49x heavy-up threshold</b> (current 0.52x).
  </div>

  <!-- ============ DMA CELL MAP ============ -->
  <span class="layer-label layer-exec">DMA cell map</span>
  <div class="card" id="dma-map-card">
    <h2>DMA cell assignments</h2>
    <div class="card-sub">Which DMAs sit in treatment vs. control across the three comparison models. Toggle to see how the control set changes.</div>
    <div class="controls">
      <div class="toggle-group" id="dma-map-toggle">
        <button class="active" data-model="matched_market">Matched Markets</button>
        <button data-model="synthetic_control">Synthetic Control</button>
        <button data-model="whole_country">Whole Country</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="width:100%;background:var(--gray-100);border-radius:8px;overflow:hidden;border:1px solid var(--gray-200);">
      <img id="dma-map-img" src="demand_gen_map_202603_matched_market.png" alt="DMA cell map — Matched Markets" style="display:block;width:100%;height:auto;">
    </div>
    <div style="display:flex;gap:22px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:14px;font-size:13px;color:var(--gray-900);">
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><span style="width:16px;height:16px;border-radius:3px;background:#c98080;border:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);"></span>Treatment DMAs</div>
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><span style="width:16px;height:16px;border-radius:3px;background:#8ecfc5;border:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);"></span>Control DMAs</div>
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><span style="width:16px;height:16px;border-radius:3px;background:#d8d8d8;border:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.1);"></span>Not included</div>
    </div>
    <p id="dma-map-desc" style="margin:14px 0 0;font-size:13px;color:var(--gray-600);line-height:1.55;">Control DMAs selected to match treatment on pre-period daily orders (MAPE + correlation). Primary model for headline iROAS.</p>
  </div>
  <script>
  (function(){
    var btns = document.querySelectorAll('#dma-map-toggle button');
    var img = document.getElementById('dma-map-img');
    var desc = document.getElementById('dma-map-desc');
    var NAMES = { matched_market:'Matched Markets', synthetic_control:'Synthetic Control', whole_country:'Whole Country' };
    var DESCS = {
      matched_market: 'Control DMAs selected to match treatment on pre-period daily orders (MAPE + correlation). Primary model for headline iROAS.',
      synthetic_control: 'Control is a weighted portfolio of donor DMAs that reconstruct the treatment counterfactual. Any DMA with a nonzero weight is shown in the control color; weight magnitude is not encoded.',
      whole_country: 'Treatment DMAs compared against the full rest-of-country. Directional validator; no hand-picked control set.'
    };
    btns.forEach(function(b){
      b.addEventListener('click', function(){
        var m = b.dataset.model;
        img.src = 'demand_gen_map_202603_' + m + '.png';
        img.alt = 'DMA cell map — ' + NAMES[m];
        desc.textContent = DESCS[m];
        btns.forEach(function(x){ x.classList.toggle('active', x === b); });
      });
    });
  })();
  </script>

  <span class="layer-label layer-exec">Layer 1 · Executive view</span>

  <!-- KPI GRID -->
  <div class="kpi-grid" id="kpi-grid"></div>

  <!-- HERO: 3-MODEL iROAS COMPARISON -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-exec">Headline</span>
    <h2>Three-model iROAS comparison</h2>
    <div class="card-sub">Matched markets is the primary model. Synthetic control and whole-country are directional validators. When all three point the same direction and magnitude, confidence strengthens. Toggle the model (orders-based is primary) and the window below.</div>
    <div class="controls">
      <div class="toggle-group" id="hero-model-toggle">
        <button data-val="orders" class="active">Orders iROAS</button>
        <button data-val="revenue">Revenue iROAS</button>
      </div>
      <div class="toggle-group" id="hero-window-toggle">
        <button data-val="trimmed" class="active">Trimmed (37d)</button>
        <button data-val="full">Full (44d)</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="chart-box h360"><canvas id="hero-chart"></canvas></div>
    <details class="math">
      <summary>Show the math · how each bar is computed</summary>
      <div class="math-body">
        <p><b>Orders iROAS</b> = (Incremental Orders × Control-cell AOV) ÷ Incremental Spend.
        <b>Revenue iROAS</b> = Incremental GP Revenue ÷ Incremental Spend. Revenue figures in our CSVs are already gross profit — no margin multiplier is applied.</p>
        <p>Incremental orders = treatment orders − (control orders × scale factor). MM scale factor this run: <b>1.1890</b>. The same orders-based SF is applied universally to orders, revenue, spend, and sessions — we do not compute per-metric SFs.</p>
        <div id="hero-math-table"></div>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <!-- DIFF VS PRIOR -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-exec">What changed since last week</span>
    <h2>Diff vs. prior run (2026-04-13)</h2>
    <div class="card-sub">One additional week of data, same test design. Green = movement in the expected direction; red = against. All 12 tracked metrics below.</div>
    <table class="dtable" id="diff-table"></table>
  </div>

  <!-- ============ LAYER 2: TACTICAL ============ -->

  <span class="layer-label layer-tac">Layer 2 · Tactical deep-dive</span>

  <!-- WEEKLY EXPLORER WITH SCRUBBER -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-tac">Week explorer · dose-response</span>
    <h2>Spend, sessions, orders — week by week</h2>
    <div class="card-sub">DG spend and sessions move together with an elasticity near 1.0. Week 5 is the clearest example: national DG spend dropped ~41%, session lift dropped ~45%. Drag the scrubber to inspect any week.</div>
    <div class="scrubber">
      <label>Week · <span id="week-label" style="font-weight: 700; color: var(--navy);">all weeks</span></label>
      <input type="range" id="week-scrub" min="0" max="6" value="0" step="1" />
      <div class="scrubber-readout" id="week-readout"></div>
    </div>
    <h3>DG spend vs. incremental sessions (weekly)</h3>
    <div class="chart-box h360"><canvas id="weekly-dose"></canvas></div>
    <details class="math">
      <summary>Show the math · elasticity and the Week 5 dose-response</summary>
      <div class="math-body">
        <p>Weekly inc DG spend and inc sessions have a Pearson correlation of <b>r = +0.98</b> across the 6-week trimmed window. Elasticity estimated as ∂ln(sessions) / ∂ln(spend) ≈ <b>~1.0</b>. In practical terms: a 40% cut in DG spend produced roughly a 40% cut in incremental sessions. Week 5 shows this cleanly — cut from ~$29k/day to ~$16k/day, session lift fell from +22% to +13%.</p>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <!-- CROSS-CHANNEL SPEND -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-tac">Where did the incremental spend go?</span>
    <h2>Cross-channel spend deltas (treatment − scaled control)</h2>
    <div class="card-sub">Validates the test: DG is the only channel with a large, directed <b>spend</b> lift. Facebook spend is slightly down in treatment (not a concern). Smaller spend lifts on Affiliates/Bing are small in absolute dollars and likely auction-side spillover. Note: the LC orders story in the next card is different — Facebook shows the biggest incremental-order halo, even on flat spend.</div>
    <div class="chart-box h360"><canvas id="spend-delta"></canvas></div>
  </div>

  <!-- CROSS-CHANNEL REVENUE -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-tac">Where did the incremental revenue come from?</span>
    <h2>Cross-channel revenue deltas (treatment − scaled control)</h2>
    <div class="card-sub">Channel-by-channel, last-click attribution — <b>GA4 (IP-based DMA resolution)</b>, which matches the matched-markets headline's DMA assignment basis. Toggle between two reads: <b>Orders Model</b> multiplies each channel's incremental order count by a single control-cell AOV ($169.04) — the same AOV used for the headline Orders iROAS. <b>Revenue Model</b> uses observed last-click GP revenue deltas directly. Shown: top 10 channels by absolute impact. Total LC incremental orders across channels reconciles within ~1% of the MM headline (+1,376).</div>
    <div class="controls">
      <div class="toggle-group" id="chrev-toggle">
        <button data-val="orders" class="active">Revenue (Orders Model)</button>
        <button data-val="revenue">Revenue (Revenue Model)</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="chart-box h420"><canvas id="chrev-chart"></canvas></div>
    <details class="math">
      <summary>Show the math · how each channel's revenue delta is computed</summary>
      <div class="math-body">
        <p><b>Orders Model (per channel):</b> inc_revenue = inc_orders × $169.04 (control-cell AOV, MM trimmed). Strips out AOV-mix noise — each channel's value is a pure order-volume translation.</p>
        <p><b>Revenue Model (per channel):</b> inc_revenue = observed last-click GP revenue in treatment − (last-click GP revenue in control × 1.189 SF). Reflects what GA4 actually recorded, AOV differences included.</p>
        <p>Source: <code>sales_by_dma_by_channel_ga4.csv</code> (GA4, IP-based DMA resolution — same basis as the matched-markets headline), trimmed window, all DMAs in test. When the two models disagree sharply on a channel, it signals an AOV shift — e.g., the treatment channel pulled in higher- or lower-ticket orders than its order-count delta suggests.</p>
        <div id="chrev-math-table"></div>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <!-- NTF SPLIT -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-tac">Who's buying — new vs. existing</span>
    <h2>NTF split: new-to-file vs. existing <span style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--gray-600); font-weight: 500;">· 1st-party last-click (secondary read)</span></h2>
    <div class="card-sub">This card uses the <b>1st-party sales file</b> because GA4 doesn't carry an NTF flag. Includes phone orders. The story still holds: this run's incremental GP concentrates on new-to-file customers, aligning with the Haus-style finding that DG is a net-new acquisition play.</div>
    <div class="chart-box h300"><canvas id="ntf-chart"></canvas></div>
    <details class="math">
      <summary>Show the math · how NTF GP is measured</summary>
      <div class="math-body">
        <p>Source: <code>sales_by_dma_by_channel.csv</code> (1st-party billing-zip resolution, includes phone orders) — the only file that carries the NTF flag. We compute trimmed-window GP dollars and orders for treatment and scaled control (SF = 1.189), split by the NTF flag, then take the delta. Last-click model — complements (does not replace) the GA4 matched-markets orders model and the GA4 cross-channel card above.</p>
      </div>
    </details>
  </div>

  <!-- PLACEMENT MIX -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-tac">Placement mix</span>
    <h2>How DG spend splits across placements, week by week</h2>
    <div class="card-sub">YouTube In-stream was the anchor placement (32–62% weekly share). Week 6 shows a drop in In-stream to 38.5% and a rise in Gmail to 19.2% — flagged as a watch item. Gmail's same-day correlation with incremental orders is slightly negative (r = −0.22), so a Gmail-heavy mix is a headwind on the LC ROAS proxy.</div>
    <div class="chart-box h360"><canvas id="mix-chart"></canvas></div>
  </div>

  <!-- CORRELATIONS -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-tac">Which placements move with orders?</span>
    <h2>Same-day and 1-day-lead placement correlations with incremental orders</h2>
    <div class="card-sub">YouTube In-stream is the strongest same-day driver (r = +0.53). YouTube In-feed leads orders by one day (r = +0.67, 1-day-lead) — a hint it may be priming conversion demand. Gmail correlations are weak or negative.</div>
    <div class="two-col">
      <div>
        <h3>Same-day correlation</h3>
        <div class="chart-box h300"><canvas id="sameday-chart"></canvas></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Lead-lag (placement leading orders by 1 day)</h3>
        <div class="chart-box h300"><canvas id="leadlag-chart"></canvas></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ============ LAYER 3: DEEP DIVE ============ -->

  <span class="layer-label layer-deep">Layer 3 · Deep-dive diagnostics</span>

  <!-- LC MULTIPLIER / WARNING THRESHOLD -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-deep">Leading indicator to watch</span>
    <h2>LC ROAS multiplier → warning threshold</h2>
    <div class="card-sub">Last-click DG ROAS is a proxy for true incrementality — we don't get a fresh geo test every week. Using this run's LC-to-true multiplier, the BAU warning threshold for DG LC ROAS is <b>0.36x</b>, and the heavy-up-level threshold is <b>0.49x</b>. Current DG LC ROAS in treatment sits at <b>0.52x</b> (GA4). If LC ROAS drops below the heavy-up threshold, pause the heavy-up until the next geo readout.</div>
    <div class="gauge-wrap">
      <div class="gauge-box"><div class="chart-box h300"><canvas id="lc-gauge"></canvas></div></div>
      <div style="flex: 1; min-width: 280px;">
        <table class="dtable" id="lc-table"></table>
        <details class="math" style="margin-top: 14px;">
          <summary>Show the math · how the warning threshold is derived</summary>
          <div class="math-body">
            <p><b>Step 1.</b> Compute this test's LC-to-true multiplier: true iROAS ÷ DG LC ROAS (treatment).</p>
            <p><b>Step 2.</b> For a 1.4x true-iROAS floor: warn when DG LC ROAS × multiplier &lt; 1.4x.</p>
            <p>→ warn threshold (orders model) = 1.4 ÷ <span id="mult-show">3.16</span> = <b>0.44x</b>.</p>
            <p>For BAU (no heavy-up), the multiplier is higher because BAU LC ROAS is typically higher relative to true iROAS — so the BAU warn threshold of 0.40x is slightly lower.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- INDUSTRY BENCHMARKS -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-deep">Is this in line with industry?</span>
    <h2>Top-line equivalent iROAS vs. published benchmarks</h2>
    <div class="card-sub">Our GP iROAS doubled is the apples-to-apples comparison to published benchmarks (since industry reports on top-line, not GP). At <b>2.92x top-line (orders)</b> and <b>4.86x (revenue)</b>, this test is above the Stella 2025 all-channel median and YouTube median.</div>
    <div class="chart-box h360"><canvas id="bench-chart"></canvas></div>
  </div>

  <!-- PRE-PERIOD FIT -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-deep">Pre-period diagnostic</span>
    <h2>Pre-period fit quality — matched markets (daily orders)</h2>
    <div class="card-sub">Treatment and scaled control should track tightly in the pre-period. MAPE is the mean absolute percentage error of the match. 13.2% orders MAPE is workable; 31.0% revenue MAPE is marginally above the 30% acceptable band (disclosed, not disqualifying).</div>
    <div class="chart-box h360"><canvas id="pp-chart"></canvas></div>
    <h3 style="margin-top: 22px;">Model-level fit diagnostics</h3>
    <table class="dtable" id="pp-table"></table>
  </div>

  <!-- FLAGS -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-deep">Flags to watch</span>
    <h2>New, resolved, and ongoing flags</h2>
    <ul class="flag-list">
      <li class="watch"><b>NEW ·</b> Revenue MAPE 31.0% marginally outside the 30% acceptable band. Disclosed, not disqualifying. Orders MAPE 13.2% remains workable.</li>
      <li class="watch"><b>NEW ·</b> Week 6 mix shift: In-stream dropped to 38.5%, Gmail rose to 19.2%. One week is not a trend. Watch next readout.</li>
      <li class="watch"><b>NEW ·</b> NTF split: new-customer GP doubled while existing-customer GP went near zero. Either a real mechanism sharpening or regression-to-mean noise. Next readout will clarify.</li>
      <li class="resolved"><b>RESOLVED ·</b> Orders iROAS cleared the 1.4x floor — 1.25x → 1.46x.</li>
      <li class="resolved"><b>RESOLVED ·</b> Synthetic control now agrees with matched markets in direction and magnitude.</li>
      <li class="resolved"><b>RESOLVED ·</b> Confidence tightened from 98.6% to effectively 100%.</li>
      <li><b>ONGOING ·</b> Orders vs. Revenue iROAS divergence (1.46x vs. 2.43x). Consistent with DG reaching higher-AOV buyers. Report both.</li>
      <li class="resolved"><b>RESOLVED ·</b> 1st-party vs. GA4 order-count sign divergence. Cross-channel read now uses GA4 (<code>sales_by_dma_by_channel_ga4.csv</code>) as primary — same IP-based DMA resolution as the MM headline. Sum of GA4 LC incremental orders ≈ +1,360, reconciling with MM headline +1,376. 1st-party retained only for NTF splits and phone-order sanity checks.</li>
      <li><b>ONGOING ·</b> $29 offer (2/25) and Iran news cycle (2/27) at the pre-period / test boundary. Effects cancel across cells but raise the noise floor.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- DECISION -->
  <div class="card">
    <span class="layer-label layer-exec">Decision & next steps</span>
    <h2>What to do</h2>
    <div class="decision">
      <div class="head">Recommended</div>
      <div class="body"><b>Continue the DG heavy-up at current levels.</b> Consider a modest step-up next cycle (5–10% spend increase) to probe the dose-response elasticity further. Keep the test running through at least 2026-05-03 to reach 60 days trimmed.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="decision" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(200,166,70,0.08) 0%, rgba(200,166,70,0.02) 100%); border-color: rgba(200,166,70,0.32);">
      <div class="head" style="color: #9e7f18;">Watch</div>
      <div class="body">DG LC ROAS in treatment. If it drops below <b>0.49x</b> (heavy-up threshold) or <b>0.36x</b> (BAU baseline), pause the heavy-up until the next geo readout. Current: <b>0.52x</b> (GA4).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="decision" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(30,54,101,0.06) 0%, rgba(30,54,101,0.02) 100%); border-color: rgba(30,54,101,0.22);">
      <div class="head" style="color: var(--navy-2);">Follow-up test</div>
      <div class="body">Once this test concludes, design a <b>placement-level follow-up</b>. Hypothesis: YouTube In-stream is carrying the incrementality; Gmail may be neutral or negative. Split-cell geo test on In-stream vs. Gmail-heavy treatment.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer class="foot">
    <div>
      Sources:
      <a href="2026-04-20_DemandGen_HeavyUp_executive-memo.md">Executive memo</a> ·
